metadata.description:
MRH + Scolla?!

SURFING SOUND?! 🏄🏽‍♂️
The D to OC?! 🍊
Channel ORNG to VibeHaus?! 🏠
a Future Surf wave?! it's only right...

Exhausted.


Produced by Noane
Artwork by Grafik (@Grxfk)
Mastered by Ashton Woods (@woods_sndz)

lyrics.text:
Ok question...
What’s in my reflection, I’m reflecting
My pen feel like my sword feel like my weapon
But I should have a pencil God is testing
He gone make me work for all my blessings...

And I, know the devil is a lie
They won’t break my soul but, I let niggas try...
I’m more into getting on I’m not into getting by
Had to watch my Granny die
She my ribbon in the sky

And I, got
Angels watching over me
First you stay down
Then you come up that’s how it’s 'posed to be
I was doing label shit before labels was approaching me
I just build a crib if they don’t open up the door for me

Like damn
I just need a chance
I got big dreams
I got big plans

Know it feel new
But I knew in advance

That money switch hands
What's up with your mans?

Running, running, running
Exhausted.
I don’t get a break from this too often

Flowers don’t come with no rain
I don’t complain
I just charge it to the game

Running, running, running
I’m exhausted
I don’t get a break from this too often

Flowers don’t come with no rain
I don’t complain
I just charge it to the game

I ain’t been seeing my demons as enemies
More like accountable energy
More like a place that I learned to escape
And a person I don’t wanna ever be
I can see all that's ahead of me
I’m too aware of my self and I’m sick for whoever ain’t here for the better me
All this serenity
Bitch I’m the perks and amenities
Word to the tribe
We like a circle of synergy
You know I’m on tip like teepee
I’m from where they bang like Chief Keef
Put it on respect and that’s on GP
Cuz I’m lit like the finger on ET
I’m here to light up the world
I’ll put it all on the line for the love of my life
And that might not be ever returned
And that thought alone settling burns
It can get heavy as sediment that be my element though
I'm in it like I’m a veteran cause in my head it’s a war
I’ve lived through sadness
I’ve lived in damage
I’ve ran in place, ran from feelings and madness
Ran from myself at a time when I needed myself and I learned to find beauty in tragic

Running, running, running
Exhausted.
I don’t get a break from this too often

Flowers don’t come with no rain
